2D724BE54DEE962822FFC2D63D70","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">When plating cells for culture, ensure that they are evenly distributed in the culture well by using a large enough volume of medium (e.g. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> per well of a 24-well plate) and shaking the plate left-to-right and top-to-bottom, avoiding circular motions that might cause cells to gather in the center. Repeat these motions once the plate has been transferred to the incubator shelf and avoid vibrations by gently closing the incubator, and ensure incubator shelves are level.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"CB4DE4D0245211EB86F299A3942274A9","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":500,"unit":"mL","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1072822,"guid":"5C77B7C0245211EB86F299A3942274A9","previous_id":1072821,"previous_guid":"5A68FC00245211EB86F299A3942274A9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C5220A05E7604292BE7A3AF8444A5BD2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Cell culture and staining: Cell staining "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B5B19C14673C4CB8A6456A67FCE14E70","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Once cells have reached approximately <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">80% confluence<\/span><span>, aspirate medium and add a standard volume of staining solution (e.g. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> for a well of a 24-well plate) to label the plasma membrane. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E164CD10245211EB86F299A3942274A9","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":500,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"2B754571D02040E0A